.TH S2REB 1NEMO "17 January 2024"

.SH "NAME"
s2reb \- convert  NEMO snapshot to rebound SimulationArchive

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBs2reb\fP [parameter=value]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBs2reb\fP converts a NEMO \fIsnapshot(5NEMO)\fP to a
rebound SimulationArchive (SA).
It currently converts all snapshots, use \fIsnaptrim(1NEMO)\fP if you
need to pre-select. Currently only mass, position and velocity are converted,
the accellerations are still ignored.

.SH "PARAMETERS"
.so man1/parameters
.TP 20
\fBin=\fP
input NEMO snapshot. No default. 
.TP
\fBout=\fP
output SimulationArchive. No default.
Note that following Rebound convention, data are appended to any pre-existing
filename, counter to the NEMO convention, which refused to overwrite.

.SH "INSTALL"
Before NEMO's rebound tools are installed, rebound needs to be installed within
NEMO. A typical install can be:
.EX

  cd $NEMO/usr/hannorein
  make install
  cd ../nemo
  make install
  
.EE
although
.EX

  mknemo -u s2reb
  
.EE
also works
